bio.summary: Demond Price  known professionally as Conway is an American rapper from Buffalo. He is the founder of Griselda Records alongside is brother Westside Gunn.
Emekwanem Ogugua Biosah Jr. (born March 29, 1990), better known by his stage name Maxo Kream, is an American rapper and record producer from Alief, Houston, Texas.
Dilated Peoples is an American hip hop group from Los Angeles, California. The group is formed by Dj Babu, Evidence and Rakaa.
Marcus Jamal Hopson (born July 18, 1985), better known by his stage name Hopsin, is an American rapper, record producer, director and actor from Panorama City, Los Angeles, California.
Kamaiyah Jamesha Johnson (born March 13, 1992) is an American rapper and singer from Sacramento, California.

Victor Santiago, Jr. (born September 6, 1977), best known by his stage name N.O.R.E., formerly Noreaga, is an American rapper. Santiago first rose to prominence as one half of the East Coast hip hop duo Capone-N-Noreaga (C-N-N), alongside fellow Queens-based rapper Capone.
Belcalis Almanzar (born October 11, 1992), known professionally as Cardi B, is an American rapper. Born and raised in Highbridge, South Bronx, New York City.
Daniel Hernandez (born May 8, 1996), known by his stage name 6ix9ine ("six-nine"), also known as Tekashi69 or simply Tekashi, is an American rapper from Bushwick, Brooklyn.
Blueprint Hakeem is a Cameroonian rapper, from the Bafut tribe in the North West Region of Cameroon.
Drakeo the Ruler is a american rapper from South Central, Los Angles, California.
L'Skadrille is a French rap band from Saint-Cyr-l'École, Yvelines. Formed in 1996 by 13or (Trésor) et 16ar (César).
03 Greedo is an American rapper/singer from Watts, Los Angeles, California.
Shayaa Bin Abraham-Joseph (born October 22, 1992), better known by his stage name 21 Savage, is an American rapper from Atlanta of Dominican and Haitian descent.
Gazzy Garcia (born August 17, 2000), known professionally as Lil Pump, is an American rapper, producer from Miami, Florida.
The Ministère AMER (Action, Musique Et Rap) is a French hip hop group from Sarcelles, consisting of the rappers Passi and Stomy Bugsy, DJ Ghetch, and the producer/manager Kenzy.
Xavier (once known as Ethelwulf) Wulf is an American rapper from East Memphis, Tennessee. Wulf was a member of the rap outfit Raider Klan.
Laïoung (born Giuseppe Bockarie Consoli, 13/08/1992), is a rapper and Italian producer. He is the cofounder of the rap crew RRR Mob.
Griby is a Ukrainian rap group from Kiev, Ukraine.
Kiernan Jarryd Forbes, known by his stage name AKA, is a South African hip hop recording artist and record producer.
Nsikayesizwe David Junior Ngcobo (born 11 February 1997), better known by his stage name Nasty C, is a South African rapper, songwriter and record producer from Durban.

Refiloe Maele Phoolo (born 16 December 1990), professionally known as Cassper Nyovest, is a South African rapper from Mahikeng. His debut album Tsholofelo was released on 18 July 2014. He is currently signed to his own independent label and media company, Family Tree.
Mohamed Bellahmed, better know as Moha La Squale (born 24 February 1995) , is a French rapper from the 20th district of Paris.

Marvin Young (born May 10, 1967), better known by his stage name Young M.C., is an English-born American singer, rapper and actor from the Queens, New York. He is best known for his 1989 hit "Bust a Move".
Kevin Abstract (born Ian Simpson; July 16, 1996), is an American rapper, singer-songwriter, and director. Abstract is a founding member of the Brockhampton band.
Woodie Smalls (born 18 June 1996) is a Belgian rapper born and raised in Sint-Niklaas, Belgium.
STR is a Belgian rapper from Bruxelles. He is a member of the 6 O'Clock Gang.
Phasm is a Belgian rapper and beatmaker from Bruxelles. He is a member of the Six o'clock Gang.
Winston Rogers III, professionally known by his stage name Tela, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. He was associated with Eightball & MJG early in his career.

Frayser Boy (born February 21, 1979) is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. At the 78th Academy Awards, he won the Academy Award for Best Original Song for "It's Hard out Here for a Pimp" along with Three 6 Mafia members Juicy J, Crunchy Black, and DJ Paul.
Lance Taylor, known as OG Boo Dirty, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee.
Adolph Thornton, Jr. (born August 11, 1985), better known by his stage name Young Dolph, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee.

Patrick Lanshaw (born October 6, 1982), better known by his stage name Lil Wyte, is an American rapper from Frayser, Memphis, Tennessee. He is a member of the rap collective Hypnotize Minds and owner of the independent label Wyte Music.

Alphonzo Bailey, better known by his stage name Al Kapone, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. Al Kapone is known principally for his underground success in the Memphis hip hop scene in the 1990s.

Patrick Houston (born February 8, 1973), better known as Project Pat is an American rapper and actor originating from Memphis, Tennessee. He is the older brother of Juicy J, the co-founder of Three 6 Mafia.

La Chat (born March 21, 1978) is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee. She is best known for her period as an artist on the Hypnotize Minds roster, and made regular guest appearances on many releases by other associated acts such as Three 6 Mafia and Gangsta Boo.

Tommy Wright III (born May 6, 1976) is a underground gangsta rapper from Memphis, Tennessee that began his career during the early 90s. He is also the head of many Memphis rap groups including the Manson Family and Ten Wanted Men.
Darnell Carlton (born August 20, 1974), better known by his stage name Crunchy Black, is an American rapper and Hype man. He was a member of the Three 6 Mafia until 2006.
Gangsta Blac, (born 11 November 1974) is a American rapper from Memphis Tennessee. His career began as a member of the Three 6 Mafia DJ Paul in Memphis before going solo in the mid 1990s.

Patrick Hall (born November 17, 1973), better known by his stage name Gangsta Pat, is an American rapper from Memphis, Tennessee who established himself in the Memphis underground during the late 1980s and is the son of Stax Records drummer, Willie Hall.
D' de Kabal (born 1974) is a french rapper, slamer, writer and director from Bobigny, Seine-Saint-Denis. He is one of the founder of the french rap group Kabal.
Roffe Ruff is a Swedish hip hop and ragga artist and music producer from Gothenburg. His real identity remains a secret, and he always wears a skull mask in his appearances.
Rakeem Calief Myer (born February 11, 1978), better known by his stage name Roc Marciano, is an American rapper, and producer.
Jermaine Eric Shute (born December 15, 1984), better known by his stage name Starlito (formerly All $tar Cashville Prince) is an American rapper from Nashville, Tennessee.
Ryszard "Peja" Andrzejewski is a Polish rap musician, songwriter and producer. He is best known as the frontman of the Polish rap group Slums Attack.
Nusky and Vaati is a french rap duo, composed of Vaati (producer) and Nusky (rapper).

Hyacinthe is a French rapper from crew DFHDGB (which stands for "Des Faux Hipster et Des Grosses Bites" and means "False Hipsters and Big Dicks") composed of rapper LOAS and beatmaker Krampf. His first album "Sarah" is out on September 29, 2017.
Patrick Losensky (born 3 April 1982), known professionally as Fler is a German rapper from West Berlin.
Anis Mohamed Youssef Ferchichi (born 28 September 1978), better known as Bushido, is a German rapper. In 2004, he and fellow rapper D-Bo founded the record label ersguterjunge.

John Edward Hawkins (November 15, 1969 – May 1, 2006), better known as H.A.W.K. or Big Hawk was an American rapper from Houston, Texas and a founding member of the late DJ Screw's rap group the Screwed Up Click.

Craig Stephen Lawson a.k.a. KLC also know as the Drum major, (born July 15, 1969) is an American record producer from the Third Ward of New Orleans, Louisiana. He found fame as a member of No Limit Records' in-house production team, Beats by the Pound.
Paul Michael Slayton (born March 11, 1981), better known by his stage name Paul Wall, is an American rapper from Houston, Texas. He is affiliated with Swishahouse Records.
Michael Jones (born November 18, 1981) is an American rapper, actor, and entrepreneur. He initially was with Swishahouse, then left to found his own label, Ice Age.
Frazier Othel Thompson III (born July 3, 1980), better known by his stage name Trae tha Truth or simply Trae, is an American hip hop recording artist from Houston, Texas.
Patrick Lamark Hawkins (December 4, 1970 – February 3, 1998), better known by his stage name Fat Pat was an American rapper from Houston, Texas.
Kenneth Doniell Moore (August 20, 1974 – October 14, 2007), better known by his stage name Big Moe, was an American rapper from Houston, Texas.

Marcus Lakee Edwards (born March 29, 1976), better known by his stage name Lil' Keke, is an American rapper from Houston, Texas and original member of the Southern hip hop collective Screwed Up Click.
Wesley Eric Weston, Jr.[1][2] (born March 3, 1981), better known by his stage name Lil' Flip, is an American rapper from Cloverland, Houston, Texas.
Michael "5000" Watts is a record producder from Houston, Texas. He is one of the founder of Swishahouse Record.
Higher Brothers are a four-man rap group from China. The members of the group are 马思唯 (MaSiWei), 丁震 (DZ), 杨俊逸 (Psy.P), and 谢宇杰 (Melo).

New African Poets (NAP) are a French hip hop group from Strasbourg. The members of the group are Mustapha, Bilal, Malik, Aïssa, Mohammed and Karim. Most of the group come from the Neuhof quartier of Strasbourg.

Craig Mack (May 10, 1970 – March 12, 2018) is an American rapper, who gained fame on Puff Daddy's Bad Boy Entertainment record label in the 1990s. Although his first single was released under the name MC EZ in 1988, he is best known for his 1994 hit single "Flava In Ya Ear", which was released under his real name.

Dead Prez, is a hip hop duo from the United States, composed of stic.man and M-1, formed in 1996 in New York City. They are known for their confrontational style, combined with socialist lyrics focused on both militant social justice, Marxism, and Pan-Africanism. The duo maintains an ethical stance against corporate control over the media, especially hip hop record labels.
Natasha Shanta Reid (born May 31, 1981), better known by her Korean name Yoon Mi-rae, is an American-born South Korean rapper and singer. She is currently a member of Korean hip hop trio MFBTY.
Jung San (Korean: 정산; born January 23, 1985), more commonly known by his stage name San E (Korean: 산이), is a South Korean rapper.

Woo Ji-ho (Korean: 우지호; born September 14, 1992), widely known by his stage name, Zico (Korean: 지코), is a South Korean rapper, producer, singer-songwriter and leader of the boy group Block B, signed under the label Seven Seasons.
Kalash l'Afro (born in Berre-l'Étang, Bouches-du-Rhône in 1979) is a French rapper of Tunisian origin.
Infinit’ is a rapper from Nice. He gained some notoriety with a song about Christian Estrosi which valued him prosecution.

Saïan Supa Crew was a French hip hop collective that was composed of three groups: Explicit Samouraï, OFX and Simple Spirit. It formed in 1997 and separated in 2007 after the departure of one of its leaders (along with Feniksi), Leeroy Kesiah.
Matthieu Balanca, known as Gérard Baste, born on January 9, 1973, is a French rapper from Paris. He is a member of the Svinkels rap group.
Soufiane elhari is a rapper singer from Rabat (CYM). He was a member of Tawra crew.
Pacewon (born Jerome Derek Hinds, Jr.) is an American rapper and producer from Newark, New Jersey. He was a member of the Outsidaz group.
Jimmy Wopo is an american rapper from Pittsburgh's Hill District in Pennsylvania.
Key is an american from Atlanta, Georgia. He is a member of the Two-9 collective.
DeAngelo Samuel, (born January 4, 1988) better known by his stage name Nyzzy Nyce (aka Nyzzy), is an American rapper from Fort Wayne, Indiana.

Louis Kevin Celestin (born August 25, 1992), known by his stage name Kaytranada, is a Haitian-Canadian DJ and record producer.
George Virden Watsky (born September 15, 1986), known professionally as Watsky, is an American hip hop artist, author, and poet from San Francisco, California.
Enzo Dong (born 01/05/1991) is a Italian rapper from Don Guanella, Naples.

Allan Kyariga (born January 6, 1994, better known by his stage name Allan Kingdom, is a Canadian rapper and record producer based in Saint Paul, Minnesota. He is a member of Thestand4rd along with Spooky Black, Bobby Raps, and Psymun.

EarthGang are an American rap duo composed of rappers Johnny "Olu O. Fann" Venus and Doctur "Eian Undrai Parker" Dot. Formed in 2008 in Atlanta, Georgia, EarthGang released its first EP, The Better Party.
GKR Is a rapper from Reykjavik, Iceland.
Ksir Makoza is a French rapper from Marseille. He was a member of the group 1K2Plus.

Pee Froiss is a hip hop group fromed Dakar, Senegal. The band's music is rapped in Wolof, French, and English and features traditional Senegalese instruments such as the kora as part of its instrumentation.

Artist Julius Dubose (born December 6, 1995), better known by his stage name A Boogie wit da Hoodie (or simply A Boogie), is an American rapper, singer, and songwriter from the Bronx, New York.
